The body of a woman found by a tour guide on Table Mountain has been identified as that of missing Cape Town lecturer Sakina Grimwood. Grimwood, 32, from Newlands, was reported missing on Wednesday. She was a lecturer at Varsity College. SABC news reported on Sunday that a tour guide had found her near a steep cliff at Platteklip Gorge on Friday. Rescue teams used a helicopter to retrieve the body. The Pink Ladies, which had circulated information about Grimwood being missing, conveyed its condolences and sympathy to the parents, family and friends. Police said a post-mortem examination would be conducted to determine the cause of death.